  "commentary": "With SPX at 6811.81 sitting above the massive negative gamma wall at 6800 (-67.6B), dealers are currently in forced buying mode as they hedge short gamma positions, which is amplifying the recent move higher. The breakout regime with -250B total GEX means dealers will continue buying rallies and selling dips, creating trending conditions with elevated volatility as we approach the positive gamma ceiling at 6840 where dealer selling pressure kicks in. Key levels to watch are the 6800 support (massive negative gamma) and 6840 resistance (max positive gamma), with the dense negative gamma cluster from 6800-6820 acting as a volatility amplification zone.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile trending moves with strong support at 6800 and resistance at 6840.",
